to that of the US armed forces. The book concludes that while the culture of the Canadian Forces has been "Americanized" to a certain extent, the culture of the US armed forces, due to changes in their personnel and roles, has experienced a certain degree of "Canadianization" at the end of the 20th and the beginning of the 21st centuries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHISTORY / Military / Canada.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357171640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773571716423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773571716/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles